member.param: Email address with optional sender name.

CC recipient email address.

Body of message.

The ID uniquely identifies the sent Email request. This filter will enable you to query delivery reports for all the messages using just one request. You will receive a bulkId in the response after sending an Email request. If you don't set your own bulkId, unique ID will be generated by our system and returned in the API response. (Optional Field)
The ID that uniquely identifies the message sent for a recipient. (Optional Field)

Template identifier based on which the email message is generated. The template is created over Infobip web interface. If templateId is present then html and text values are ignored. NOTE : This field supports value of broadcast templateId only.Content templateId is not supported.
File attachment
Using an inline image, it is possible to insert the image file inside the HTML code of the email by using cid:FILENAME instead of providing any external link to image.
HTML body of the message. If HTML and text fields are present, text field will be ignored and HTML will be delivered as message body.
Email address to which recipients of the email can reply.
Default placeholder values used for all recipients. The values are used to generate the email message.
This parameter enables preserving To recipients for an email when value is true, default value is false for this parameter.

The URL on your callback server on which the open and click notifications will be sent. If you are passing this parameter then track=true will be assigned, you don't need to pass track=true separately. See the section "Tracking Notifications" below for details.
This parameter enables or disables track click feature.
This parameter enables or disables track open feature.

Enable or disable open and click tracking.Default value is true. Passing true will only enable tracking and the statistics would be visible in web interface alone. This can be explicitly overridden by trackopens and trackclikcs.
Additional client data that will be sent on the notifyUrl. The maximum value is 4000 characters.
The real-time Intermediate delivery report that will be sent on your callback server.
The URL on your callback server on which the Delivery report will be sent.
Preferred Delivery report content type. Can be application/json or application/xml.

member.summary: Get outbound SMS message delivery reports. If you are for any reason unable to receive real-time delivery reports on your endpoint, you can use this API method to learn if and when the message has been delivered to the recipient. Each request will return a batch of delivery reports - only once. The following API request will return only new reports that arrived since the last API request in the last 48 hours.
member.remarks: [Learn more about SMS channel and use cases.](https://www.infobip.com/docs/sms)
member.param: Request payload
Cancellation Token to cancel the request.See .

member.summary: Get outbound SMS message logs. Use this method for displaying logs for example in the user interface. Available are the logs for the last 48 hours and you can only retrieve maximum of 1000 logs per call. See [message delivery reports](https://www.infobip.com/docs/api#channels/sms/get-outbound-sms-message-delivery-reports) if your use case is to verify message delivery.
member.remarks: [Learn more about SMS channel and use cases.](https://www.infobip.com/docs/sms)

An array of message objects of a single message or multiple messages sent under one bulk ID.

Limits the send speed when sending messages in bulk to deliver messages over a longer period of time. You may wish to use this to allow your systems or agents to handle large amounts of incoming traffic, e.g., if you are expecting recipients to follow through with a call-to-action option from a message you sent. member.name: T:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.SmsBinaryMessage
member.summary: SmsBinaryMessage
Initializes a new instance of the class.
member.param: SMS binary content.

Additional data that can be used for identifying, managing, or monitoring a message. Data included here will also be automatically included in the message Delivery Report. The maximum value is 4000 characters and any overhead may be truncated.
Sets specific scheduling options to send a message within daily or hourly intervals.
An array of destination objects for where messages are being sent. A valid destination is required.

Allows for sending a flash SMS to automatically appear on recipient devices without interaction. Set to true to enable [flash SMS](https://www.infobip.com/docs/sms/message-types#flash-sms), or leave the default value, false to send a standard SMS.
The sender ID which can be alphanumeric or numeric (e.g., CompanyName). Make sure you don't exceed [character limit](https://www.infobip.com/docs/sms/get-started#sender-names).
The real-time intermediate delivery report containing GSM error codes, messages status, pricing, network and country codes, etc., which will be sent on your callback server. Defaults to false.
Preferred delivery report content type, application/json or application/xml.

The URL on your call back server on to which a delivery report will be sent. The retry cycle for when your URL becomes unavailable uses the following formula: 1min + (1min * retryNumber * retryNumber). [Delivery report format](https://www.infobip.com/docs/api#channels/sms/receive-sent-sms-report)
Region-specific parameters, often imposed by local laws. Use this, if country or region that you are sending an SMS to requires additional information.
Date and time when the message is to be sent. Used for scheduled SMS. Has the following format: yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ. Must be sooner than 180 days from now.

The message validity period in minutes. When the period expires, it will not be allowed for the message to be sent. Validity period longer than 48h is not supported. Any bigger value will automatically default back to 2880.

member.summary: Initializes a new instance of the class.
member.param: Indicates whether multiple PIN verification is allowed. (Default: true)
Number of possible PIN attempts. (Default: 10)

Validity period of PIN in specified time unit. Required format: {timeLength}{timeUnit}. timeLength is optional with a default value of 1. timeUnit can be set to: ms, s, m, h or d representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours, and days respectively. Must not exceed one year, although much lower value is recommended. (Default: "15m")

Overall number of requests over a specified time period for generating a PIN and sending an SMS using a single application. Required format: {attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}. attempts is mandatory and timeLength is optional with a default value of 1. timeUnit is one of: ms, s, m, h or d representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours, and days respectively. Must not exceed one year, although much lower value is recommended. (Default: "10000/1d")

Number of requests over a specified time period for generating a PIN and sending an SMS to one phone number (MSISDN). Required format: {attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}. attempts is mandatory and timeLength is optional with a default value of 1. timeUnit is one of: ms, s, m, h or d representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours, and days respectively. Must not exceed one year, although much lower value is recommended. (Default: "3/1d")

The number of PIN verification requests over a specified time period from one phone number (MSISDN). Required format: {attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}. attempts is mandatory and timeLength is optional with a default value of 1. timeUnit is one of: ms, s, m, h or d representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours, and days respectively. Must not exceed one day, although much lower value is recommended. (Default: "1/3s")

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.AllowMultiplePinVerifications
member.summary: Tells if multiple PIN verifications are allowed.

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.PinAttempts
member.summary: Number of possible PIN attempts.

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.PinTimeToLive
member.summary: PIN time to live. Should be in format of `{timeLength}{timeUnit}`. Here `timeLength` is an optional positive integer with a default value of 1 and `timeUnit` is one of: `ms`, `s `, `m`, `h` or `d` representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours and days respectively. Must not be larger that one year, although much lower values are recommended.

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.SendPinPerApplicationLimit
member.summary: Overall number of requests in time interval for generating a PIN and sending an SMS using single application. Should be in format of `{attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}`. Here `attempts` is a mandatory positive integer and `timeLength` is an optional positive integer with a default value of 1. ` timeUnit` is one of: `ms`, `s`, `m`, `h` or `d` representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours and days respectively. Time component must not be larger that one year, although much lower values are recommended.

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.SendPinPerPhoneNumberLimit
member.summary: Number of requests in time interval for generating a PIN and sending an SMS to one phone number (MSISDN). Should be in format of `{attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}`. Here `attempts` is a mandatory positive integer and `timeLength` is an optional positive integer with a default value of 1. `timeUnit` is one of: `ms`, `s`, `m`, `h` or `d` representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours and days respectively. Time component must not be larger that one year, although much lower values are recommended.

member.name: P:Infobip.Api.SDK.SMS.Models.TfaApplicationConfiguration.VerifyPinLimit
member.summary: Number of PIN verification requests in time interval from one phone number (MSISDN). Should be in format of ` {attempts}/{timeLength}{timeUnit}`. Here `attempts` is a mandatory positive integer and ` timeLength` is an optional positive integer with a default value of 1. `timeUnit` is one of: ` ms`, `s`, `m`, `h` or `d` representing milliseconds, seconds, minutes, hours and days respectively. Time component must not be larger that one day, although much lower values are recommended.
